author: cbs8
title: Truck spins off road, overturns, ejects driver; he dies
text:
KROTZ SPRINGS, La. (AP) - State police say a 58-year-old man died after his truck spun out and overturned on Louisiana Highway 105, throwing him out north of Krotz Springs.
Master Trooper Brooks David (dah-VEED) says Jeffery Nall of Krotz Springs was heading south on Louisiana Highway 105 when the car ran off to the right, overcorrected and spun off the other side.
He says Nall's 1999 Ford truck crashed early Sunday, and Nall died at a hospital.
David says impairment is suspected, and toxicology samples were taken. David also says Nall was not wearing a seat belt.
